"v.使(人)极为愤怒 【英】 v.使(人)极为愤怒(en rage) 【记】 in(进入)+furi(=fury 狂怒)+ate→进入狂怒 【例】 Mary infuriated Bob by insulting him in public. v. 使(人)极为愤怒 = enrage 【记】in进入, furi = fury(n 狂怒; 狂暴), ate－进入狂怒状态 【类】infuriate: rage = commend: esteem = nonplus: perplexity激怒: 大怒 = 称赞: 尊敬 = 困惑: 困惑『scrounge: possession』『v 占有: n 占有』 【记】in, en 使 + fury 狂怒；fur 毛，毛发，皮毛 引申为怒发(冲冠) 【相关】fury 狂怒，furious 狂怒的, 狂暴的, 激烈的 infuriate (v.)  1660s, from Italian infuriato, from Medieval Latin infuriatus, past participle of infuriare ""to madden,"" from Latin in furia ""in a fury,"" from ablative of furia (see fury). Related: Infuriated; infuriating; infuriatingly."
